# Project Stack & Coding Conventions

EmbedKit is a **frontend-only clickable prototype** in `frontend/`. There is no backend. All persistence is mock data and Zustand in-memory state.

Follow these conventions for all TypeScript, JavaScript, TSX, and JSX files under `frontend/src/`.

## Technical Stack

- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode, no implicit `any`)
- **Runtime**: React 19
- **Build**: Vite 8
- **Routing**: React Router 7 (`createBrowserRouter`)
- **State**: Zustand 5 (`frontend/src/common/stores/app.store.ts`)
- **Styling**: CSS Modules (`*.module.css`) + design tokens in `frontend/src/index.css`
- **Testing**: Vitest + Testing Library + jsdom
- **Linting / formatting**: ESLint + Prettier
- **Path alias**: `@/` ‚Üí `frontend/src/`

**Not used in this project:** Shadcn, Yup, Lucide React, backend frameworks.

## Naming Conventions

- **Variables & functions**: `camelCase`
- **Components & types / interfaces**: `PascalCase`
- **Files**: kebab-case (e.g. `bot-card.tsx`, `mock-chat.utils.ts`)
- **Domain values**: TypeScript `enum` in `frontend/src/common/enums/`. Do not model the same domain values as string-literal unions in types or stores ‚Äî use the enum type instead.

## API, Error Handling & Data Validation

- **JSDoc**: Document all public functions using JSDoc.
- **Error handling**: Never swallow errors. Use Result-type patterns or throw meaningful, descriptive errors.
- **Validation**: Prototype auth uses local validators in feature utils (e.g. `auth.utils.ts`), not Yup.

## Development Workflow

- **Test-first for new logic**: Add mocks and unit tests before or alongside implementation.
- **TDD cycle**: Write the test, verify failure, then implement.
- **Mandatory verification** (run from `frontend/`):
  1. `npm run build` ‚Äî must pass
  2. `npm run lint` ‚Äî must pass
  3. `npm run test` ‚Äî 100% pass rate for affected logic

## Architecture & Design Decisions

- Refer to `docs/` when suggesting architectural changes or new features.
- This repo is a **prototype**, not a full-stack app. Do not introduce backend layers unless explicitly requested.

### Feature-Based Organization

Business UI and logic live in `frontend/src/features/`. Each feature is self-contained with its own components, constants, utils, styles, and tests.

Shared code used across features lives in `frontend/src/common/`, grouped by role:

| Directory | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- |
| `common/components/` | Reusable UI primitives (`Button`, `Modal`, `BotNav`, ‚Ä¶) |
| `common/constants/` | App-wide constants and mock seed data |
| `common/enums/` | Domain enums (`PlanTier`, `PaywallTrigger`, ‚Ä¶) |
| `common/hooks/` | Shared React hooks |
| `common/stores/` | Zustand global store |
| `common/types/` | Shared TypeScript types |
| `common/utils/` | Cross-feature utilities |

`frontend/src/app/` holds the router and root app shell.

### File Role Suffixes

Use clear suffixes inside features:

| Suffix | Role |
| :--- | :--- |
| `.constants.ts` | Copy, limits, static config |
| `.utils.ts` | Pure helpers and business rules |
| `.module.css` | Scoped styles |
| `.test.ts` / `.test.tsx` | Unit / component tests |
| `*-page.tsx` | Route-level page component |
| `*-gate.tsx` | Plan-gated wrapper (analytics, settings, widget) |

